  "texts": [
    "The fact that participants could identify the AI without interactive dialogue is impressive since interactivity would likely bring more opportunities for differentiation.",
    "We made this choice to increase experimental control while still preserving a high degree of ecological richness in passage content.",
    "Despite this limitation, this format is still generalizable to many real-world contexts in which human judges might not necessarily interrogate the agent, such as queries for moral advice from a typical search engine.",
    "However, future research could extend this work by introducing an interactive component.",
    "Furthermore, our test did not prompt the AI to imitate a human speaker in order to actively deceive the judge, diverging again from some versions of a traditional Turing Test."
  ],
